<h2 id="intro" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#intro"><span>Intro</span></a></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>CSS - Cascading Style sheets</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Cascading style sheets are called <em>cascading</em> because several different style sheets can be active for a single document at the same time. When multiple style sheets are in effect, they are applied to the document in a pre-determined sequence set by the browser: their formatting instructions can be thought of as cascading from one style sheet to the next.</p>
</blockquote>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>NOT</strong> a programming language</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Style sheet/Styling language</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Used for website <strong>style design</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Can be extended with Sass/Less</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>User experience</strong> of content matters</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
